    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>With the platypus, Tachyglossa are the only egg-laying mammals. The female lays a single soft-shelled, leathery egg, deposits it directly into her pouch, where there are no nipples, but after hatching the young echidna sucks milk from the pores of the two milk patches.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
